Key Match Events: Shohei Ohtani hit a go-ahead two-run homer in the bottom of the fifth
Teoscar Hernandez put the boys in blue right back ahead with a go-ahead solo shot
Ryan McMahon hit a go-ahead homer in the top of the fifth
Mookie Betts followed Ohtani’s homer up by casually flipping a 100mph fastball over the left-field wall
Others: The Dodgers are still determined to stay ahead of the San Diego Padres and clinch the National League West division title
Much has been made out of Ohtani’s addition to the Dodgers’ already deep and dangerous lineup with hopes he can help them get over the hump this postseason
If he continues his clutch hitting, Hernandez could end up being the lineup addition that breaks the annual curse of Dodger bats freezing up in October
With so many rotation arms continuing to be on the shelf and the bullpen having to endure a high workload, Buehler’s growth in stretching himself out coming off Tommy John is encouraging
If he can eat up innings and compete in October, that will do wonders for a Dodger rotation that desperately needs it
The Dodgers found themselves down 5-1 early and still trailed 5-4 heading into the bottom of the ninth

Back-to-back home runs to win a game is not something seen every day, but that’s exactly what the Dodgers will need in the postseason given the perennial target on their back: improbable exciting feats of stardom in desperate moments
Luckily, they have a roster full of players who can provide just that
